### Order Processing API Test Suite

# Base URL for local development
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

###
# ==================== CUSTOMER ENDPOINTS ====================
###

### Create Customer 1 - Alice
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Alice Johnson",
  "email": "alice.johnson@example.com"
}

###

### Create Customer 2 - Bob
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Bob Smith",
  "email": "bob.smith@example.com"
}

###

### Create Customer 3 - Charlie
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Charlie Brown",
  "email": "charlie.brown@example.com"
}

###

### Get Customer by ID (Alice)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### List All Customers
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Update Customer (Alice - change name)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Alice M. Johnson",
  "email": "alice.johnson@example.com"
}

###
# ==================== ADDRESS ENDPOINTS ====================
###

### Add Home Address for Alice (Customer 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1/addresses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "label": "home",
  "addressLine1": "123 Main Street",
  "addressLine2": "Apt 4B",
  "city": "Austin",
  "state": "TX",
  "postalCode": "73301",
  "country": "USA"
}

###

### Add Work Address for Alice (Customer 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1/addresses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "label": "work",
  "addressLine1": "456 Corporate Blvd",
  "city": "Austin",
  "state": "TX",
  "postalCode": "73302",
  "country": "USA"
}

###

### Add Home Address for Bob (Customer 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/2/addresses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "label": "home",
  "addressLine1": "789 Oak Avenue",
  "city": "Dallas",
  "state": "TX",
  "postalCode": "75201",
  "country": "USA"
}

###

### Add Billing Address for Bob (Customer 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/2/addresses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "label": "billing",
  "addressLine1": "321 Pine Road",
  "city": "Fort Worth",
  "state": "TX",
  "postalCode": "76102",
  "country": "USA"
}

###

### List Addresses for Alice (Customer 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1/addresses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### List Addresses for Bob (Customer 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/2/addresses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Remove Work Address for Alice (Customer 1, Address 2)
### Response: 204 No Content (even if address doesn't exist - idempotent)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1/addresses/2
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###
# ==================== ORDER ENDPOINTS ====================
###

### Create Order 1 - Alice with home address
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "addressId": 1,
  "items": [
    {
      "productName": "Laptop",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 999.99
    },
    {
      "productName": "Wireless Mouse",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 29.99
    }
  ]
}

###

### Create Order 2 - Bob with home address
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": 2,
  "addressId": 3,
  "items": [
    {
      "productName": "Monitor 27-inch",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 349.99
    },
    {
      "productName": "USB-C Cable",
      "quantity": 3,
      "unitPrice": 15.99
    }
  ]
}

###

### Create Order 3 - Charlie (needs address first)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/3/addresses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "label": "home",
  "addressLine1": "555 Elm Street",
  "city": "Houston",
  "state": "TX",
  "postalCode": "77001",
  "country": "USA"
}

###

### Create Order 3 - Charlie with home address
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": 3,
  "addressId": 5,
  "items": [
    {
      "productName": "Mechanical Keyboard",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 149.99
    },
    {
      "productName": "Desk Lamp",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 49.99
    }
  ]
}

###

### Get Order by ID (Order 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### List All Orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### List Orders Filtered by Status (PENDING)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders?status=PENDING
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### List Orders Filtered by Status (PROCESSING)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders?status=PROCESSING
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Update Order Status - Order 1 to PROCESSING
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1/status
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "status": "PROCESSING"
}

###

### Update Order Status - Order 2 to SHIPPED
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/2/status
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "status": "SHIPPED"
}

###

### Try to Cancel Non-Pending Order (Should Fail - Order 1 is PROCESSING)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1/status
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "status": "CANCELLED"
}

###

### Cancel Pending Order 3 via Status Endpoint
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/3/status
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "status": "CANCELLED"
}

###

### Cancel Order 2 via POST /cancel (Create new PENDING order first)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "addressId": 1,
  "items": [
    {
      "productName": "USB Hub",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 39.99
    }
  ]
}

###

### Cancel Order 4 via DELETE /api/orders/{id} — returns 200 with CANCELLED status (PENDING only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/4
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Try to Cancel Already-Cancelled Order (Should Return 400)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/4
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Try to Get Cancelled Order (Should Return 200 with CANCELLED status)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/4
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###
# ==================== ERROR CASES ====================
###

### Try to Create Duplicate Customer Email (Should Return 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Duplicate User",
  "email": "alice.johnson@example.com"
}

###

### Try to Create Order with Non-Existent Customer (Should Return 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": 999,
  "addressId": 1,
  "items": [
    {
      "productName": "Test Item",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 10.00
    }
  ]
}

###

### Try to Create Order with Invalid Address (Should Return 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "addressId": 999,
  "items": [
    {
      "productName": "Test Item",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 10.00
    }
  ]
}

###

### Try to Create Order with Empty Items (Should Return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "addressId": 1,
  "items": []
}

###

### Try to Get Non-Existent Customer (Should Return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/999
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Try to Add Address to Non-Existent Customer (Should Return 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/999/addresses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "label": "test",
  "addressLine1": "Test St",
  "city": "Test City",
  "state": "TS",
  "postalCode": "00000",
  "country": "USA"
}

